description:
The world's first super-team returns in this volume collecting the first 4 issues of the all-new Justice Society Of America series, written by Geoff Johns with stunning art by Dale Eaglesham & Art Thibert and a cover by Alex Ross! Determined to rebuild the Justice Society, founding members Green Lantern, Flash and Wildcat initiate an unprecedented recruitment program, tracking the bloodlines of heroes across the world and bringing in the new Starman, Damage, Liberty Belle and more! But just as the Society welcomes the rookies into their ranks, an evil force sets out to destroy them. Meet new legacies, solve a mystery stretching into the far future, witness the return of the world's greatest hero and watch another one fall in this fantastic collection!   

This series has been collected in the following trade paperbacks:

  • Justice Society Of America: The Next Age - (#1-4)

description:
A series that reprinted landmark moments in X-Men history to celebrate 35 years of X-Men comics.  Each issue came with a foil cover to heighten the collectibility. 
 
The series reprints:  

  • The first two appearances of the X-Men as the face off against Magneto & the Vanisher in X-Men #1 & #2;
  • The Days Of Future Past storyline from Uncanny X-Men #141 & #142; 
  • The culmination of the Dark Phoenix Saga in Uncanny X-Men #137; 
  • The climax of the Fatal Attractions crossover, including the removal of the Adamantium from Wolverine's body & Professor X mind-wiping Magneto from X-Men #25; 
  • The first appearance of the All-New, All-Different X-Men as they come together & battle Krakoa the Living Island in Giant-Size X-Men #1; and 
  • The moment the Acolytes form around Magneto who establishes Asteroid M as a haven for mutants in X-Men #1.
name: Marvel Collectible Classics: X-Men

description:
It turns out the famous voice actor Sonny Strait (of Dragonball Z and Full Metal Alchemist fame) is also a cartoonist! Sonny's '''We Shadows''' is an manga-style fantasy, and a sequel to A Midsummer Night's Dream (sorry Shakespeare, we couldn't wait). It can also be found online (in part) at weshadows.com .

"There is a song–it is a key to unlocking a gateway into a world of Shadows. A dark yet magical place where faeries, ogres and hobgoblins co-exist. One such creature is Goat, a homely being considered insane by the others. Her only friend is a talking mushroom who assures her she is a 'fairy princess in training.' However the truth of Goat’s destiny is far more interesting… Follow Goat as she unlocks the secret of her origins and her untapped power–a world of magic is just a song away!"

Original English-Language (OEL) manga.
name: We Shadows

description:
Original English-Language (OEL) manga.

In this game, it's the players who are being played...

Imagine a world where all your flaws and imperfections could be erased. An entire universe where you could be anyone or anything you want. Now stop imagining -- the World of Hartz is here.

Han has always had trouble with real life. He's irresponsible, shy and far too obsessed with video games. However, when he jacks into the new Hartz gaming system, Han becomes a virtual hero.

When Han becomes too engrossed with Hartz, his best buddy, T, goes online to confront him. But the linkup proves to be a mind-blowing trip when the true nature of the game is finally revealed.

The World of Hartz can be everything you want it to be. Come on -- you know you want to play.
name: World of Hartz
